-- ArcelorMittal South Africa's CFO Kobus Verster Resigns, Switches to Aveng
-- Amanda Jordan
-- 2010-07-23T06:44:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/arcelormittal-south-africa-says-verster-resigns-as-chief-financial-officer.html

          
          
             ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd. 
Chief Financial Officer  Kobus Verster  will resign and take up a
position at Aveng Group.  
 Verster will step down from ArcelorMittal South Africa on
Aug. 23, the steelmaker said today in a statement, without
giving a reason for his departure. Verster has been appointed an
executive director at Aveng starting Sept. 1 and financial
director from Sept. 27, the construction company said in a
separate statement.  
 ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd., a unit of the worldâ€™s
largest steel producer, named  Rudolph Torlage  as acting CFO.
Torlage, currently general manager of controlling, will hold his
new position until the board names a permanent replacement, the
Vanderbijlpark-based company said in the statement.  
